title: Moderate U.S. consumer spending, inflation support rate cut
text: U.S. consumer spending and prices rose moderately in June, pointing to slower economic growth and benign inflation that could see the Federal Reserve cutting interest rates on Wednesday for the first time in a decade.

title: Futures drop as eyes shift to Fed meeting, Apple earnings

title: Goldman Sachs ups S&P 500 forecast but cuts earnings outlook
text: Goldman Sachs raised its 2019 year-end price target for the U.S. benchmark S&P 500 index by 3% to 3,100 points on Tuesday.

title: Stormy sterling sinks again, stocks wilt before Fed
text: Brewing no-deal Brexit worries sent the pound sinking towards a two-year low versus the euro and roughed up Irish bonds on Tuesday, while stock markets wilted before what is expected to be the first cut in U.S. rates since the financial crisis.

title: Huawei Technologies posts 23% H1 revenue growth amid U.S. sanctions
text: China's Huawei Technologies [HWT.UL] said on Tuesday revenue in the first half of the year grew 23.2% - faster than a year ago -  despite an intense U.S. campaign against it that ultimately became a trade ban from mid-May.

title: Telecoms lobby demands access to high-band spectrum for 5G
text: The global telecoms industry on Tuesday demanded access to the high-capacity spectrum it says it needs to support data-intensive 5G services, accusing the space lobby of hogging frequencies in a way that could stunt the technology.

title: Huawei says its first-half revenue jumped 23.2% despite political headwinds
text: China's Huawei said its total revenue came in at 401.3 billion yuan ($58.26 billion) and its net profit margin for the period was 8.7%.

title: Oil prices rise amid expectations that U.S. Fed will cut rates
text: Oil prices rose for a fourth day on Tuesday on optimism the U.S. Federal Reserve will this week cut interest rates for the first time in more than ten years, which should support economic and fuel demand growth in the world's biggest oil user.

title: As trade war bites, China's factories set for third month of shrinking activity
text: Factory activity in China is expected to have contracted for the third month in a row in July, a Reuters poll showed, underlining the intensifying strains on the world's second-biggest economy from a protracted trade war with the United States.
